Airline Business Analysis and future prediction based on passengers' satisfaction¶

Project 2 for Group 8:¶

Team members: Sahand Yousefi- Siddharth Dwivedi¶

Data: https://www.kaggle.com/teejmahal20/airline-passenger-satisfaction¶

Abstract¶

In this day and age, transportation industry is considered as a vital feature for economy, so finding new ways to enhance revenue as well as profit, is common and turned to competition between transportation companies. Since, the first step to increase the amount of profit is customer attraction, this project is done by considering an airline customers' satisfaction because as a general rule: the more satisfaction, the more attraction. This project will be performed to analayze and compare previous trends of passengers' satisfaction and finally predict future trends by using regression model. From where we stand, airlines' owners as well as managers can be percieved by our analysis and we tend to believe that, they will be more focus on customer satisfaction in future. Finally, we will try to answer some important questions to evaluate this project's efficiency. These questions are listed below:

A. Descriptive Questions:¶

Our first question(Descriptive) based on the dataset that we have is:

  • Could airline to get acceptable level of satisfaction of its customers?

  • which factor had more effect on customers' satisfaction?

B. Diagnostic Questions:¶

and our Diagnostic question is:

  • why some factors like drink and food or distances had effect on customers' satisfaction?

  • our statistical analysis like variance analysis can be efficient to explain the trend of satisfaction, or not?

Note:¶

In the Kaggle the name of dataset is mentioned "train" while the dataset is for airline and airplains, so we changed the name to "airline"

1. Introduction¶

As the infromation that explained in abstract, dataset is for an airline passengers evaluated their satisfaction level in terms of some features which are listed below:¶

  • Gender: Gender of the passengers (Female, Male)

  • Customer Type: The customer type (Loyal customer, disloyal customer)

  • Age: The actual age of the passengers

  • Type of Travel: Purpose of the flight of the passengers (Personal Travel, Business Travel)

  • Class: Travel class in the plane of the passengers (Business, Eco, Eco Plus)

  • Flight distance: The flight distance of this journey

  • Inflight wifi service: Satisfaction level of the inflight wifi service (0:Not Applicable;1-5)

  • Departure/Arrival time convenient: Satisfaction level of Departure/Arrival time convenient

  • Ease of Online booking: Satisfaction level of online booking

  • Gate location: Satisfaction level of Gate location

  • Food and drink: Satisfaction level of Food and drink

  • Online boarding: Satisfaction level of online boarding

  • Seat comfort: Satisfaction level of Seat comfort

  • Inflight entertainment: Satisfaction level of inflight entertainment

  • On-board service: Satisfaction level of On-board service

  • Leg room service: Satisfaction level of Leg room service

  • Baggage handling: Satisfaction level of baggage handling

  • Check-in service: Satisfaction level of Check-in service

  • Inflight service: Satisfaction level of inflight service

  • Cleanliness: Satisfaction level of Cleanliness

  • Departure Delay in Minutes: Minutes delayed when departure

  • Arrival Delay in Minutes: Minutes delayed when Arrival

  • Satisfaction: Airline satisfaction level(Satisfaction, neutral or dissatisfaction)

2. Main (Analysis)¶

Analysis is performed in three phases including "Check", "Comparison" and "prediction". In first phase we try to present our dataset better by showing its basic information including shape,info,head,tail and etc. In the second phase we are going to analayze the dataset in terms of Descriptive analytics and Diagnostic analytics, by using statistical tools such as bar charts or histograms and etc. Ultimately, in the last phase we use statistical methods like regression line to predict future trends. Then conclusion is explained at the end of the third phase, so main part is consisted of some sub-parts.

2.2 Second Phase: "Analysis"¶

In this phase we are going to make comparison between criterias having effects on passengers' satisfaction level. To make efficient comparison, its specific chart or figure is drawn.

Important point is that, our second phase is consisted of two steps: Descriptive Analysis and Diagnostic Analysis. But before checking our dataset features and making comparison together with their explanation. Firstly, we checked our dataset in terms of some attributes which were not included in our survey from passenfers like "Age" and their "type of Flight".

Analysis including descriptive as well as diagnostic are important steps for conducting statistical analysis. It gives you an idea of the distribution of your data, helps you detect outliers and types, and enable you identify associations among variables, thus making you ready to conduct further statistical analyses. Descriptive statistics or descriptive analytics can be efficient for two purposes: 1) to provide basic information about variables in a dataset and 2) to highlight potential relationships between variables. The three most common descriptive statistics can be displayed graphically or pictorially and are measures of: Graphical/Pictorial Methods.

Descriptive statistics help us to simplify large amounts of data like our dataset in a sensible way. Each descriptive statistic reduces lots of data into a simpler summary. For instance, consider a simple number used to summarize how well a batter is performing in baseball, the batting average.

Explanation of figure one:¶

Figure one is consisted of four bar charts and in this section we are going to explain and analysis each of them, respectively.

Online boarding:¶

Totally the performance of airline was not bad in this regard, even the most proportion of passengers who were dissatisfied chose score 3 in survey while almost 2500 of passengers who were dissatisfied, chose 5 out of 5. As expectations, satisfied passengers chose 4 and 5, more than other choices. Actually, almost 37000 of satisfied passengers, were satisfied about online boarding service,too. On the other hand, almost 9000 of satisfied passengers, were not satisfied about this service during their experience with the airline.

Seat comfort:¶

In this scope of analysis, number of satisfied passengers who had not intresting experience, did not have change significantly. Actually, almost 9000 of satisfied passengers chose scores lower than 4 in this regard while none of them chose score 0. Constantly, almost 10000 as well as 15000 of dissatisfied of passengers had excellent and good experience about their seat, respectively. Also, none of dissatisfied passengers chose 0, actually they had a minimum percent af satisfaction.

Inflight entertainment:¶

This service should be more considered in airline because some proportion of passengers who even were satisfied of their experiences about the airline, identified 3 and lower for scores.

On-board service:¶

Number of dissatisfied passengers was considerable. But most proportion of dissatisfied passengers had "middle" opinion about the On-board service and most proportion of satisfied passengers gave "4".

3. Conclusion¶

Our conclusion can be devided to some parts such as follows.

Summary of findings:¶

A) In this project we found that level of customers' satisfaction can be depends on many features. Evaluating satisfaction in each of them can lead to efficient overview about customers' opinion and total satisfaction level about the airline.

B) We found that some features have considerable correlation with each other. To be more exact, "Ease_of_Online_booking" is highly correlated with "Inflight_wifi_service". Also "Inflight_service" is highly correlated with "Baggage_handling". On the other hand, some feature including "Delay" can have impressive impact on customers' satisfaction

C) We found the factor "Age" can make changes on passengers' expectations, actually passengers with different ages have different criterias for evaluating airline.

Business implications for audience:¶

The project was done in manner that can be understandable for technical and non-technical audiences, contacts and readers. It is clear that airline for attracting more proportion of passengers should make its progress online, more than before. Passengers showed great passion for identifying their flight's details online. Apart from this, it can decrease airline expenses.

Limitations of this project:¶

The main limitation that we faced was the number of passnegers, if it would be more, it could be better. Secondly, the number of evaluation were divided between 0 and 5 by the airline while it could be more range to better approximation. some factors was not considered in airline survey like "safety" that is important for every airline passenger.

Answer of our questions:¶

In this part we answered our questions that were mentioned in abstract section, separately.

Descriptive questions:¶

1- Unfortunately, not. Airline could not get acceptable level of satisfaction based on the number of passengers. It is shown clearly on 'comparing passengers in terms of satisfaction' bar chart. most proportion of passengers were dissatisfied about their experineces in airline.

2- As mentioned in the "heat map" flight entertainment had more effect in attracting passengers satisfaction level while " Delay" had considerable negative effect in declining passengers satisfaction level.

Diagnostic questions:¶

1- Because passengers need to feel conveninece when they want to have travel. To reach this convenience, many factors should be considered. These factor could be minor like the quality of drink in flight or could be more major like the amount of delay.

2- In this project, the analysis of variance could not be efficient as much as using heatmap. because all the passnegers were examined in a survey devided between 0 and 5 and due to the number of passnegers participated in survey, it could not be efficient for analysis and prediction.

Suggestion for potential projects:¶

  • Adding-up some other features for having better approximation such as "Safety" and "Child Service"
  • Making wider the range of survey from 0 to 5. It could be better in terms of using some prediction models.
  • After making the range of survey wider, analysis of variance can be made to have better prediction.
